---
import LayoutFunnel from '@/layouts/LayoutFunnel.astro';
---

<LayoutFunnel title="Luxury Revenue Architecture | Marketing by Besic">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-brand/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-brand" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 3v4M3 5h4M6 17v4m-2-2h4m5-16l2.286 6.857L21 12l-5.714 2.143L13 21l-2.286-6.857L5 12l5.714-2.143L13 3z" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <h1 class="heading-xl mb-6">
        Your OTA Commissions Are Eating 40% of Your Margin. We Eliminate That.
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        Booking.com takes 15-25% of every reservation. Your property is worth EUR 800/night but your acquisition cost makes it a EUR 600 business. Direct bookings fix the math.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-hero.webp" alt="Luxury Revenue Architecture" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-12 object-cover max-h-[500px]" width="1200" height="500" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Three Revenue Leaks Eroding Your Luxury Margins</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 1: 60-80% of Bookings Through OTAs</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Booking.com, Expedia, and Airbnb Luxe take 15-25% commission on every reservation. On a EUR 50K revenue month, you're paying EUR 7,500-12,500 in commissions. That's not a distribution cost -- that's a structural margin problem. And it compounds every month.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 2: Digital Experience Doesn't Match the Price Tag</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Your property charges EUR 800/night but your website looks like a EUR 150/night hotel. Stock photos. Generic booking widget. "Check availability" button. A UHNWI client spending EUR 15K on a week's stay expects a digital experience that matches the physical one. Yours doesn't.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 3: Standard E-Commerce UX Insulting High-Net-Worth Clients</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            "Add to cart." "Book now." "Select dates." This is Amazon UX applied to a EUR 50K experience. High-net-worth clients don't "book now" -- they request access. Your booking flow is commoditizing your premium positioning and repelling the clients who would pay the most.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Image -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-problem.webp" alt="Luxury brand revenue leak diagnosis" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">The Exclusionary Revenue Architecture</h2>

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: Direct Booking Diagnostic</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We calculate your total OTA commission cost, map your direct booking conversion rate, and identify exactly how much revenue you're surrendering to intermediaries. Most luxury properties discover they're losing EUR 100K+ annually in commissionable revenue that should be direct.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: Exclusionary UX Architecture</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              "Request an Audience" replaces "Book Now." Bespoke digital experience that mirrors the physical one. Invitation-only access tiers. Curated photography that sells the feeling, not the room count. We rebuild your digital presence so it commands the same respect as your property.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: Direct Acquisition System</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Retargeting, PR placement, and content omnipresence designed for UHNWI audiences. Not "luxury travel blog" SEO -- direct outreach to family offices, concierge services, and the private networks where EUR 50K+ bookings originate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Image -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-solution.webp" alt="Exclusionary Revenue Architecture system" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution Gap Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#111111] relative z-10">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Most Agencies Deliver Reports. We Deliver Revenue.</h2>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center">
        The gap between knowing your OTA dependency is killing you and actually building direct booking infrastructure is where luxury properties stall for years. Your last agency "optimized your website." Your OTA ratio didn't move. Our framework closes the execution gap by rebuilding the entire guest acquisition system.
      </p>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center font-semibold text-brand">
        We rebuilt the UX for a luxury mansion platform where average transactions exceed EUR 50K. We replaced "Book Now" with "Request an Audience."
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 pb-48">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-6">Apply for a Revenue Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        We work with luxury hospitality brands generating EUR 2M+ annually who are ready to reclaim their margins from OTA intermediaries. If that's you, apply below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center w-full">
        <a
          href="/en/apply"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-white transition-all duration-300 bg-[#8224e3] rounded-lg hover:bg-[#6a1ca6] hover:scale-105 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(130,36,227,0.4)]"
        >
          Apply for Revenue Diagnosis
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutFunnel>
